Take a look at the following code and select the corresponding output of the console:

```java
import java.util.ArrayList;
import java.util.List;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        List<String> exampleList = new ArrayList<>();
        exampleList.add("This");
        exampleList.add("list");
        exampleList.add("has");
        exampleList.add("size");
        System.out.print(exampleList + " " + exampleList.size());
    }
}
```

In which order will the numbers be printed to the console?

```java
import java.util.Stack;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Stack<Integer> stack = new Stack<>();
        stack.push(53);
        stack.push(23);
        stack.push(24);
        stack.push(42);
        while (!stack.isEmpty()) {
            System.out.print(stack.pop() + "; ");
        }
    }
}
```

Take a look at the following code snippet. Which statements are correct?

```java
import java.util.HashSet;
import java.util.Set;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Set<String> princesses = new HashSet<>();
        princesses.add("Snow White");
        princesses.add("Cinderella");
        princesses.add("Ariel");
        princesses.add("Cinderella");
        princesses.add("Aurora");
        for (String princess : princesses) {
            System.out.print(princess + "; ");
        }
    }
}
```
